HEADWORD: Syngenesis
<hw>Syn*gen"e*sis</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>syn-</ets> + <ets>genesis</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Biol.)</fld> <def>A
theory of generation in which each germ is supposed to contain the germs
of all subsequent generations; -- the opposite of
<contr>epigenesis</contr>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

